Route 22.Notes: This route is technically optional, though you probably want the Pokémon catch here before the first gym.

Trainers.Notes: Last fight of Reflection Cave. Occurs after you come back up from B1F.

Elite Four.Notes:
The Elite Four may be challenged in any order you choose.

However, because of the addition of the Mobile PC, you are able to adjust your team between fights.

The choice to do so is ultimately up to you, but the intended design is that your team will be locked in upon entering the Elite 4, as per the base game.

Trainers.Notes:
For Illusion purposes, Entei is the set as the last member of the party.

This can mean that Zoroark copies either Entei or Diancie, as the AI will always send the mega out last.

Lumiose Parade.Notes:
I'm not sure whether most players will consider the challenge complete upon defeating Diantha or upon defeating AZ.

As such, I leave it up to you to choose whether or not you wish to consider AZ optional or mandatory.

Trainers.Notes: While you cannot change your party before AZ, your team will be fully healed.
